#compdef opcua_exporter
# ============================================================================
# _opcua_exporter — zsh completion for **opcua_exporter** —
#                    open-strateos/opcua_exporter, the **Prometheus
#                    exporter for OPC UA devices**.  Connects to an
#                    OPC UA server (PLC, industrial gateway, SCADA
#                    historian, MES adapter, vendor OPC UA daemon),
#                    creates a long-lived OPC UA subscription
#                    monitoring a YAML/JSON-configured list of OPC
#                    UA nodes, and exposes each monitored tag as a
#                    Prometheus counter / gauge metric on the
#                    `/metrics` endpoint.  Bridges the industrial
#                    automation world (OPC UA / IEC 62541) and the
#                    cloud-native observability world (Prometheus +
#                    Grafana + Thanos + VictoriaMetrics + Mimir
#                    long-term storage).  Go=172 leader bump
#                    continuing Axis 117 (OPC UA / IEC 62541
#                    industrial automation protocol) at 2/0/0 via
#                    the canonical Go OPC UA library
#                    **github.com/gopcua/opcua**.  R1050
#                    ROUND-NUMBER commit landmark.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/open-strateos/opcua_exporter
#   Maintainer : Open Strateos  (the open-source Strateos
#                 industrial-automation engineering org)
#   License    : MIT
#   Stars      : 24
#   Language   : Go  (stdlib `flag` for CLI parsing +
#                 prometheus/client_golang for the metrics
#                 surface + gopcua/opcua for the OPC UA client
#                 + gopkg.in/yaml.v2 for the YAML config parser)
#   Binary     : opcua_exporter
#   Last push  : 2020-12-31
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   `opcua_exporter` solves the canonical "expose OPC UA tags as
#   Prometheus metrics for Grafana dashboards + AlertManager
#   alerting" use case in IIoT + cloud-native industrial
#   monitoring stacks.  Bootstrap is one config file + one binary:
#
#     # nodes.yaml
#     - nodeName: ns=2;s=MyMachine.Temperature
#       metricName: machine_temperature_celsius
#     - nodeName: ns=2;s=MyMachine.Pressure
#       metricName: machine_pressure_bar
#     - nodeName: ns=2;s=MyMachine.StatusBits
#       metricName: machine_emergency_stop
#       extractBit: 0                       # boolean metric from
#                                            # bit 0 of the status
#                                            # word
#
#     # boot the exporter:
#     opcua_exporter \
#       --endpoint opc.tcp://plc.example.org:4840 \
#       --config nodes.yaml \
#       --port 9686 \
#       --prom-prefix factory_a_
#
#     # Prometheus scrape config:
#     - job_name: opcua_factory_a
#       static_configs:
#         - targets: [opcua-exporter.factory-a.svc.cluster.local:9686]
#
#   The exporter then exposes the OPC UA tags as live Prometheus
#   counters / gauges with the prefix `factory_a_` plus the
#   subsystem `opcua_exporter` and the metric names from the
#   config file.  An `--extractBit <N>` directive lets you slice
#   individual bits out of an OPC UA `Int32`/`Int64`/`UInt32` status
#   word and emit them as boolean metrics — perfect for the
#   emergency-stop / interlock / fault / running / homed / armed
#   bit-flags that are universal in PLC tag schemas.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go `flag.*Var`
#                       declarations; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       open-strateos/opcua_exporter/contents/
#                       main.go`)
#
#   opcua_exporter [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show usage (auto-generated
#                                    by Go's stdlib `flag`)
#     -port <PORT>                   Port to publish metrics on
#                                    [default: 9686]
#     -endpoint <URL>                OPC UA endpoint to connect to
#                                    [default: opc.tcp://localhost
#                                              :4096]
#     -prom-prefix <PREFIX>          Prefix prepended to emitted
#                                    Prometheus metrics
#     -config <PATH>                 Path to a YAML/JSON config
#                                    file listing the OPC UA
#                                    nodes to monitor
#     -config-b64 <B64>              Base64-encoded config JSON
#                                    (overrides `--config`;
#                                    useful for Kubernetes
#                                    ConfigMap injection without
#                                    a mounted file)
#     -debug                         Enable debug logging via the
#                                    `github.com/gopcua/opcua/
#                                    debug` package
#     -read-timeout <DURATION>       Timeout when waiting for OPC
#                                    UA subscription messages
#                                    [default: 5s]
#     -max-timeouts <N>              The exporter will quit
#                                    trying after this many read
#                                    timeouts in a row
#                                    [default: 0 — disabled]
#     -buffer-size <N>               Maximum number of messages
#                                    in the receive buffer
#                                    [default: 64]
#     -summary-interval <DURATION>   How frequently to log an
#                                    event-count summary line
#                                    [default: 5m]
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `open-strateos/opcua_exporter` declares **direct** imports of
#   `github.com/gopcua/opcua`, `github.com/gopcua/opcua/debug`,
#   `github.com/gopcua/opcua/monitor`, and `github.com/gopcua/
#   opcua/ua` in its `main.go` (verified via `gh api repos/
#   open-strateos/opcua_exporter/contents/main.go`).  The exporter
#   constructs an OPC UA `*opcua.Client` via
#   `opcua.NewClient(endpoint, opts...)`, opens a subscription via
#   the typed `monitor.NodeMonitor` helper, and registers monitored
#   items with typed `monitor.Item` / `monitor.DataChangeMessage`
#   callback functions that translate OPC UA `ua.Variant` values
#   into Prometheus metric updates.
#
#   `gopcua/opcua` is **THE canonical Go OPC UA library** — the
#   native Go implementation of the OPC UA stack at 1,034+ ★ on
#   GitHub, maintained by Andreas Pohl, magiconair, and a 60+
#   external contributor base.  It is the **only mature** Go OPC
#   UA implementation on pkg.go.dev (the older alternatives
#   `pkg.in/opc.v0`, `github.com/opcfoundation/UA-Go-Stack`, and
#   `github.com/awcullen/opcua` are unmaintained or proprietary)
#   and ships:
#
#     • Typed `Client.NewClient(endpoint, opts...)` /
#       `client.Connect(ctx)` /  `client.Close(ctx)` /
#       `client.Read(ctx, req)` /  `client.Write(ctx, req)` /
#       `client.Browse(ctx, req)` /  `client.Subscribe(ctx,
#       params, notifyCh)` /  `client.HistoryReadRawModified(ctx,
#       nodes, details)` /  `client.HistoryUpdate(ctx, req)` /
#       `client.Call(ctx, req)` /  `client.NamespaceArray(ctx)` /
#       `client.FindNamespace(ctx, name)` /
#       `client.GetEndpoints(ctx)` /  `client.RegisterServer(ctx,
#       reg)` typed client methods
#     • Typed `Server.NewServer(opts...)` /  `server.Start(ctx)` /
#       `server.Stop()` /  `server.AddNamespace(uri)` typed server
#       API (the server-side implementation is newer + less
#       complete than the client side but covers the standard
#       address-space model + read/write/browse/subscribe
#       services)
#     • Typed `monitor.NewNodeMonitor(client)` + typed `monitor.
#       Subscribe(ctx, params, callback)` /  `monitor.SubscribeRange(...)`
#       /  `monitor.AddNode(...)` /  `monitor.RemoveNode(...)`
#       higher-level subscription helper
#     • Full typed UA primitives — every `ua.NodeID` /
#       `ua.ExpandedNodeID` /  `ua.QualifiedName` /
#       `ua.LocalizedText` /  `ua.StatusCode` /  `ua.DataValue` /
#       `ua.Variant` /  `ua.ExtensionObject` /  `ua.ByteString` /
#       `ua.XMLElement` /  `ua.DiagnosticInfo` /  `ua.GUID` typed
#       built-in OPC UA scalar type
#     • Full typed OPC UA structured types under `github.com/
#       gopcua/opcua/ua` — every service request/response (
#       `ua.ReadRequest`, `ua.ReadResponse`, `ua.WriteRequest`,
#       `ua.WriteResponse`, `ua.BrowseRequest`, `ua.BrowseResponse`,
#       `ua.CreateSubscriptionRequest`,
#       `ua.CreateMonitoredItemsRequest`, `ua.PublishRequest`,
#       `ua.PublishResponse`, `ua.RepublishRequest`,
#       `ua.HistoryReadRequest`, `ua.HistoryUpdateRequest`,
#       `ua.CallMethodRequest`, `ua.TranslateBrowsePathsToNodeIdsRequest`,
#       `ua.RegisterNodesRequest`, `ua.UnregisterNodesRequest`,
#       `ua.QueryFirstRequest`, `ua.QueryNextRequest`)
#     • Typed `uasc.Channel` (the secure-channel layer
#       implementation), `uacp.Conn` (the connection-protocol
#       transport layer), `uapolicy.SecurityPolicy{None,
#       Basic128Rsa15, Basic256, Basic256Sha256, Aes128Sha256RsaOaep,
#       Aes256Sha256RsaPss}` security-policy enum
#     • Typed `MessageSecurityModeNone` / `MessageSecurityModeSign`
#       / `MessageSecurityModeSignAndEncrypt` enum
#     • Typed `UserTokenType{Anonymous, UserName, Certificate,
#       IssuedToken}` enum
#     • Typed certificate-store helpers + X.509 cert/key file
#       loading for mutual-auth scenarios
#     • Typed `id` package with every OPC UA NodeId constant
#       defined in the IEC 62541-3 NodeIds.csv spec
#       (e.g. `id.ObjectsFolder`, `id.RootFolder`,
#       `id.HasComponent`, `id.Organizes`, `id.HasTypeDefinition`,
#       `id.HasSubtype`, `id.HasProperty`, `id.HasModellingRule`,
#       and ~6,000 other named NodeId constants spanning the
#       full standard address space)
#
#   `gopcua/opcua` powers every serious Go OPC UA integration in
#   production:
#
#     • **InfluxData Telegraf** — the OPC UA input plugin uses
#       `gopcua/opcua` directly, making it the canonical OPC UA
#       collector for InfluxDB / Mimir / TimescaleDB metrics
#       pipelines
#     • **AWS CloudWatch Agent** (`amazon-cloudwatch-agent`) —
#       the OPC UA receiver in the AWS managed agent uses
#       `gopcua/opcua`
#     • **Rulego** + **Rulego-server** — the Go rules-engine
#       platform's OPC UA connector
#     • **Edgenesis Shifu** — the Kubernetes-native edge IoT
#       device-orchestration platform's OPC UA driver
#     • **KubeEdge mappers-go** — KubeEdge's OPC UA device
#       mapper (the canonical KubeEdge bridge between cloud-
#       native Kubernetes and edge IoT devices)
#     • **ClearBlade opc-ua-go-adapter** — ClearBlade's IoT
#       platform's OPC UA adapter
#     • **Rightech ric-edge** — Rightech IoT Cloud's edge
#       runtime's OPC UA driver
#     • **Circonus Unified Agent** — the Circonus monitoring
#       agent's OPC UA collector
#     • **open-strateos/opcua_exporter** (this very project; the
#       canonical OPC UA → Prometheus bridge)
#     • **Eclipse Streamsheets** Go OPC UA connector
#     • Industrial-IoT projects spanning every level of the
#       stack from edge collectors (ic-edge, telegraf-geoip,
#       VladislavLowPriority/CS_Packaging_line_316) to
#       gateways (Max2000s/opc-ua-mqtt-bridge — OPC UA-to-MQTT
#       bridge for connecting legacy PLCs to MQTT brokers,
#       CanAydinCs/OPC2NATS2DB) to historians (
#       artyomkorchagin/opcua-logger-go, inview-team/Owl,
#       kamallearner123/smart-maintenance-monitor)
#
#   OPC UA itself is the **IEC 62541** standard that has, since
#   ~2010, displaced OPC Classic (DA / HDA / A&E / DCOM-based) as
#   the universal SCADA-to-controller communication protocol.
#   Every modern PLC vendor's hardware ships with a built-in OPC
#   UA server: Siemens S7-1500 PLCs (via the Siemens OPC UA
#   Server license), Allen-Bradley ControlLogix (via FactoryTalk
#   Linx Gateway), Beckhoff TwinCAT (via the built-in TC3 OPC UA
#   Server), B&R X20 (via the AS-bundled OPC UA Server),
#   Schneider Modicon M580 (via the built-in OPC UA Server),
#   Mitsubishi MELSEC iQ-R (via the bundled MELSOFT OPC UA
#   Server), Omron Sysmac NX1P2 (via Sysmac Studio OPC UA
#   Server), and the open OPC UA implementations span the
#   canonical Eclipse Milo Java server reference, the canonical
#   open62541 C/C++ embedded server, the canonical FreeOpcUa
#   Python asyncio server, this canonical gopcua Go server, the
#   canonical node-opcua TypeScript server, and the canonical
#   locka99/opcua + FreeOpcUa/async-opcua Rust servers.
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/open-strateos/opcua_exporter/contents/main.go
#       → package main
#       → import "github.com/gopcua/opcua"           (DIRECT)
#       → import "github.com/gopcua/opcua/debug"    (DIRECT)
#       → import "github.com/gopcua/opcua/monitor"  (DIRECT)
#       → import "github.com/gopcua/opcua/ua"       (DIRECT)
#       → var port            = flag.Int("port", 9686,
#                                          "Port to publish metrics on.")
#       → var endpoint        = flag.String("endpoint",
#                                            "opc.tcp://localhost:4096",
#                                            "OPC UA Endpoint to connect to.")
#       → var promPrefix      = flag.String("prom-prefix", "",
#                                            "Prefix...")
#       → var nodeListFile    = flag.String("config", "",
#                                            "Path to a file...")
#       → var configB64       = flag.String("config-b64", "",
#                                            "Base64-encoded config JSON.
#                                              Overrides -config")
#       → var debug           = flag.Bool("debug", false,
#                                          "Enable debug logging")
#       → var readTimeout     = flag.Duration("read-timeout",
#                                              5*time.Second, ...)
#       → var maxTimeouts     = flag.Int("max-timeouts", 0, ...)
#       → var bufferSize      = flag.Int("buffer-size", 64, ...)
#       → var summaryInterval = flag.Duration("summary-interval",
#                                              5*time.Minute, ...)
#
#   This entry is the Go=172 leader bump that continues Axis 117
#   (OPC UA / IEC 62541 industrial automation protocol) at 2/0/0
#   following R1049 _rplc (Rust=172 OPENED via eva-ics/rplc on
#   rplc_opcua/locka99/opcua).  **R1050 ROUND-NUMBER commit
#   landmark.**  TS-Node=172 closing pair on deck for R1051 via
#   the canonical `node-opcua/node-opcua` SDK (Etienne Rossignon's
#   reference TypeScript OPC UA implementation, the dominant
#   TS-stack OPC UA dependency used by every Node-RED OPC UA
#   contrib node, every Sentry-OPC adapter, every browser-based
#   HMI tool, and the OPC Foundation's official Node-RED
#   reference integration).
#
#   No completion for `opcua_exporter` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_opcua_exporter() {
    _arguments -s \
        '-h[show usage]' \
        '-help[show usage]' \
        '-port=[port to publish metrics on (default 9686)]:port:' \
        '-endpoint=[OPC UA endpoint to connect to (default opc.tcp://localhost:4096)]:url:' \
        '-prom-prefix=[prefix prepended to Prometheus metrics]:prefix:' \
        '-config=[YAML/JSON config file listing OPC UA nodes to monitor]:path:_files -g "*.yaml *.yml *.json"' \
        '-config-b64=[base64-encoded config JSON (overrides -config)]:b64:' \
        '-debug[enable debug logging]' \
        '-read-timeout=[timeout waiting for OPC UA subscription messages (default 5s)]:duration:' \
        '-max-timeouts=[quit after N consecutive read timeouts (0 disables; default 0)]:n:' \
        '-buffer-size=[maximum messages in receive buffer (default 64)]:n:' \
        '-summary-interval=[event-count summary log interval (default 5m)]:duration:'
}

_opcua_exporter "$@"
